[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello,  is there a standard way to handle C structs that are packed that contain structs that have bitfields? For example the C struct</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"C\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">hv_nested_enlightenments_control</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n                <span class=\"n\">__u32</span> <span class=\"nl\">directhypercall</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n                <span class=\"n\">__u32</span> <span class=\"nl\">reserved</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">31</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">features</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n                <span class=\"n\">__u32</span> <span class=\"n\">reserved</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">hypercallControls</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">__packed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>gets generated to </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[repr(C, packed)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Default, Copy, Clone)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">hv_nested_enlightenments_control</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">features</span>: <span class=\"nc\">hv_nested_enlightenments_control__bindgen_ty_1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hypercallControls</span>: <span class=\"nc\">hv_nested_enlightenments_control__bindgen_ty_2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"cp\">#[repr(C)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[repr(align(4))]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Default, Copy, Clone)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">hv_nested_enlightenments_control__bindgen_ty_1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_bitfield_1</span>: <span class=\"nc\">__BindgenBitfieldUnit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"k\">usize</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">hv_nested_enlightenments_control__bindgen_ty_2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">reserved</span>: <span class=\"nc\">__u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This isn't allowed in rust since \" a <code>packed</code> type cannot contain another type with the <code>align</code><br>\nrepresentation\" from E0588</p>",
        "id": 242240266,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Teuttli",
        "timestamp": 1623345351
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you don't need to actually read these fields, there's an option in bindgen to tell it to treat the struct as an opaque blob.</p>",
        "id": 242240956,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1623345656
